OL,3,CHealth fund which provides free
OL,4,Cprescriptions is 'unsustainable'
OL,6,FThe Auditor General adds that with no
OL,7,Fprice controls, GP surgeries are free
OL,8,Fto charge whatever they deem
OL,9,Facceptable for appointments - meaning
OL,10,Fthat higher fees could wipe out any
OL,11,Fbenefit to patients from increased
OL,12,Fsubsidies.
OL,14,FShe states there have been examples of
OL,15,Fprices rising over inflation between
OL,16,FFebruary 2024 and July 2025.
OL,18,FIn response, the Government says it is
OL,19,Fconsidering reforming the Health
OL,20,FInsurance Fund.
